Description: FRagment of neck and oval handle rising to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-grey. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '135'. Name Agesarchos. The same die is used for an example from Olbia Pontica and for Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0307.33.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (52)
